Meanwhile, the WRC Safari Rally Serivce Park at the KWS Training Institute in Naivasha has been hailed at one of the largest in the world and the surface measuring 110 by 220 metres has been tarmacked in readiness to host manufacturer teams from Ford, Toyota and Hyundai.However, fans will be restricted because of Covid-19 protocols, of course unless a vaccine is found soon!